"{\"uid\": \"complex.com-pop-culture-a-markelibert-watch-tom-cruise-jump-from-stade-de-france-to-close-out-2024-paris-summer-olympics\", \"text\": \"SHOP CYBER MONDAY  GET THE APP  STYLE  MUSIC  SNEAKERS  SPORTS  LIFE  SHOWS  Tom Cruisehelped close out the2024 Paris Summer Olympicswith a massive stunt that saw him participate in skydiving off the Stade de France.  On Sunday, the city of Paris, France, officially closed out the 2024 Summer Olympics, and the actor gave them a hand to pass over the event to the next host city, Los Angeles. For the stunt, Cruise wore a harness and jumped off the top of the Stade de France and onto the stadium grounds, where athletes cheered and greeted him.  Los Angeles Mayor Karen Bass and seven-time gold medal gymnastSimone Bilesthen handed Cruise the Olympic flag, which he attached to the back of a motorcycle, and rode off into a video that highlighted his journey to the City of Angels.  Cruise rode past various Parisian landmarks, such as the Eiffel Tower in the video, and ended up on a plane where he changed into some skydiving gear before jumping out of it and onto the legendary Hollywood sign. He then changed the sign's letter O into the Olympic rings and handed the flag to Olympic cyclist Kate Courtney, who took it through LA with assistance from Olympians Michael Johnson and Jagger Eaton.  The whole montage ended with Courtney arriving at a performance by Red Hot Chili Peppers, Snoop Dogg, Dr. Dre, and Billie Eilish. The upcoming 2028 Summer Olympics games will take place from July 14 to July 30, with the opening and closing ceremonies at SoFi Stadium and the Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum, respectively.  pop-culture| BYMark Elibert  Rob Lowe Reflects on Tom Cruise Once Knocking Him Out During 'The Outsiders' Filming  pop-culture| BYJoe Price  Glen Powell Recalls Tom Cruise Pranking Him by Pretending to Lose Control of Helicopter, Dropping Altitude  pop-culture| BYAlex Ocho  Tom Cruise Apparently Started Breakdancing at Victoria Beckham's Birthday Party and Left Crowd 'Dumbfounded'  Stay ahead onExclusives  Download the Complex App  Follow On  Sign Up for the Newsletter  By entering your email, you agree to receive customized marketing messages from us and our advertising partners. You also acknowledge that this site is protected by reCAPTCHA, and that ourPrivacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.  COMPLEX participates in various affiliate marketing programs, which means COMPLEX gets paid commissions on purchases made through our links to retailer sites. Our editorial content is not influenced by any commissions we receive. \\u00a9 Commerce Media Holdings, LLC All Rights Reserved.\"}"